The paper deals with dynamic algorithms for maintaining spectral vertex sparsifiers of graphs, which involves data structures and algorithms for maintaining pairwise resistances, solutions to systems of linear equations, and energy of electrical flows between terminals. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS), numerical analysis (cs.NA), computational geometry (cs.CG), social and information networks (cs.SI), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
